This was a great pick me up after an early morning flight & a couple of hours of sightseeing. It was healthy & affordable, easy in & out no frills food. I had the salad bowl & brother had a pita sandwich. He felt it was on the small side but had chosen to omit vegetables so... My salad was more than adequate in size. Staff was friendly, restaurant was spotless, pita bread was soft & moist. Perfect.

Having just spent several weeks in the Middle East and eating tons of traditional food, I can say with some authority that the offerings at NafNaf seem quite authentic and similarly delicious. I ordered a bowl with a hummus base, a mix of chicken schwarma and falafel, topped with their delicious traditional salad, red cabbage and pickles. I chose Tahini and Harissa as my sauces. The Tahini was just a bit runnier than it should be but the flavor was terrific. The pita bread that came with dinner was the most delicious pita I think I’ve ever had anywhere. Tasted freshly baked! I will definitely be back to NafNaf!
Hands down the best Mediterranean food I've ever had, including nearby locales, such as Nesh. But it gets busy. You'll want to arrive here on the early side to get a good meal in a timely fashion.

This place has gone WAY downhill. Rice was hard, undercooked, and extremely salty. Chicken had a massive piece of fat in it, like huge. The piece was pure fat and it was bigger than any other piece. Super disgusting. The rice was terrible. Sad to see such a great place doing such a bad job.
